<section class="starter-library">
  <header class="starter-library__hero">
    <p class="starter-library__eyebrow">Starter template documentation</p>
    <h1>Theme component library</h1>
    <p>
      A built-in reference page for developers and merchants. Use it to see what this theme includes,
      where each piece lives, and which files to customize.
    </p>
    <div class="starter-library__route">
      <span>Page template</span>
      <code>templates/page.starter-library.json</code>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="starter-library__note">
    <strong>Included by default:</strong>
    this theme ships with <code>templates/page.starter-library.json</code>, including the visual demo sections below.
    Shopify still requires a page record in the admin to expose a store URL. Create any page and assign the
    <code>starter-library</code> template, or preview it with <code>/pages/page-handle?view=starter-library</code>.
  </div>

  <nav class="starter-library__nav" aria-label="Library navigation">
    <a href="#library-guide">How to use</a>
    <a href="#library-sections">Sections</a>
    <a href="#library-infrastructure">Infrastructure</a>
    <a href="#library-templates">Templates</a>
    <a href="#library-snippets">Snippets</a>
    <a href="#library-assets">Assets</a>
    <a href="#library-blocks">Theme blocks</a>
  </nav>

  <div class="starter-library__summary">
    <div>
      <strong>19</strong>
      <span>Standalone sections</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>20</strong>
      <span>Portable public blocks</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>14</strong>
      <span>Theme templates</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>21</strong>
      <span>Reusable snippets</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>26</strong>
      <span>Theme assets</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  {% capture starter_showcase_modal_content %}
    <p>This content is passed into the modal snippet through a Liquid capture.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Use it for forms, product details, size guides, or rich content.</li>
      <li>The same snippet accepts your own custom trigger markup.</li>
    </ul>
  {% endcapture %}
  {% capture starter_showcase_modal_trigger %}
    <button class="starter-library-modal-trigger" type="button">
      <span>Open snippet demo</span>
      <small>Custom modal trigger</small>
    </button>
  {% endcapture %}
  {% capture starter_showcase_consent_label %}
    <p>I agree to be contacted about my request.</p>
  {% endcapture %}
  {% capture starter_showcase_topic_options %}Sizing
Shipping
Returns{% endcapture %}
  {% capture starter_showcase_priority_options %}Low
Medium
High{% endcapture %}
  {% assign starter_demo_product = all_products['gift-card'] %}
  {% assign starter_demo_blog = blogs['news'] %}
  {% assign starter_demo_article = starter_demo_blog.articles.first %}
  {% assign starter_search_label = 'search.title' | t %}
  {% assign starter_search_placeholder = 'search.placeholder' | t %}
  {% assign starter_search_submit = 'search.submit' | t %}
  {{ 'predictive-search.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
  <script src="{{ 'predictive-search.js' | asset_url }}" defer></script>

  <section class="starter-library__group" id="library-guide">
    <header class="starter-library__heading">
      <p>How to use this library</p>
      <h2>Composition map</h2>
    </header>

    <div class="starter-library__guide-grid">
      <article class="starter-library-guide-card">
        <span>1</span>
        <h3>Start with the wrapper</h3>
        <p>
          Use <code>sections/base-section-container.liquid</code> when a page area needs editable spacing,
          max-width, side padding, background color, gradient, or background image.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="starter-library-guide-card">
        <span>2</span>
        <h3>Add portable blocks inside</h3>
        <p>
          Content components in <code>blocks/*.liquid</code> are block-only by design. They should not
          include their own <code>&lt;section&gt;</code> tag or container wrapper.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="starter-library-guide-card">
        <span>3</span>
        <h3>Keep route sections standalone</h3>
        <p>
          Product, collection, cart, header, footer, search, and account-like infrastructure sections stay
          as sections because they own page-level behavior or Shopify route data.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="starter-library-guide-card">
        <span>4</span>
        <h3>Read the reference below</h3>
        <p>
          Each component starts with a visual or practical example, then lists where the implementation lives
          and how to apply it in templates or the theme editor.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="starter-library__note">
      <strong>Rule of thumb:</strong>
      if a component is portable page content, build it as a block and place it inside
      <code>Base section + container</code>. If it controls a route, global area, drawer, or product-specific
      behavior, keep it as a section.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="starter-library__group" id="library-sections">
    <header class="starter-library__heading">
      <p>Sections and portable blocks</p>
      <h2>Store-building components</h2>
    </header>

    <div class="starter-library__note">
      <strong>Reading this list:</strong>
      this section is now a map, not a fake preview gallery. Real portable block examples are rendered below
      by <code>templates/page.starter-library.json</code> as actual <code>base-section-container</code> sections
      with real <code>blocks/*.liquid</code> children. Paths beginning with <code>sections/</code> are standalone
      route or wrapper owners.
    </div>

    <div class="starter-library__table" role="table">
      <div class="starter-library__row starter-library__row--head" role="row">
        <span role="columnheader">Live demo source</span>
        <span role="columnheader">Real blocks rendered below</span>
        <span role="columnheader">Notes</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <code role="cell">templates/page.starter-library.json</code>
        <span role="cell"><code>hero</code><code>media-with-text</code><code>featured-collection</code><code>product-slider</code></span>
        <span role="cell">Merchandising and campaign blocks render as actual theme blocks inside Base section + container.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <code role="cell">templates/page.starter-library.json</code>
        <span role="cell"><code>trust-badges</code><code>collection-list</code><code>logo-marquee</code><code>promo-grid</code></span>
        <span role="cell">Composite blocks render with their real private child blocks.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <code role="cell">templates/page.starter-library.json</code>
        <span role="cell"><code>faq</code><code>featured-blog</code><code>testimonials</code><code>comparison-table</code><code>tabs</code></span>
        <span role="cell">Support, content, social proof, comparison, and tab examples are live block instances.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <code role="cell">templates/page.starter-library.json</code>
        <span role="cell"><code>group</code><code>text</code><code>newsletter</code><code>newsletter-promo</code><code>contact-form</code></span>
        <span role="cell">Primitive layout, text, and form examples are real editable blocks.</span>
      </div>
    </div>

  </section>

  <section class="starter-library__group" id="library-infrastructure">
    <header class="starter-library__heading">
      <p>Standalone sections</p>
      <h2>Route and global owners</h2>
    </header>

    <div class="starter-library__table" role="table">
      <div class="starter-library__row starter-library__row--head" role="row">
        <span role="columnheader">Area</span>
        <span role="columnheader">Primary files</span>
        <span role="columnheader">Why it stays a section</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <span role="cell">Header and footer</span>
        <span role="cell"><code>sections/header.liquid</code><code>sections/header-group.json</code><code>sections/footer.liquid</code><code>sections/footer-group.json</code></span>
        <span role="cell">Global theme-group owners for navigation, search entry points, menus, and footer content.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <span role="cell">Product route</span>
        <span role="cell"><code>sections/product.liquid</code><code>sections/product-recommendations.liquid</code><code>sections/sticky-add-to-cart.liquid</code></span>
        <span role="cell">Owns product object data, media gallery, variant state, recommendations, and add-to-cart behavior.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <span role="cell">Collection and search routes</span>
        <span role="cell"><code>sections/collection.liquid</code><code>sections/collections.liquid</code><code>sections/search.liquid</code><code>sections/predictive-search.liquid</code></span>
        <span role="cell">Owns Shopify route data, filters, sorting, search results, predictive search, and pagination.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <span role="cell">Cart surfaces</span>
        <span role="cell"><code>sections/cart.liquid</code><code>sections/cart-drawer.liquid</code></span>
        <span role="cell">Owns cart lines, drawer state, Ajax rendering, notes, attributes, discounts, and checkout entry.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <span role="cell">Content routes</span>
        <span role="cell"><code>sections/page.liquid</code><code>sections/blog.liquid</code><code>sections/article.liquid</code></span>
        <span role="cell">Owns page, blog, and article route data plus SEO-oriented article/card rendering.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <span role="cell">Utility routes</span>
        <span role="cell"><code>sections/404.liquid</code><code>sections/password.liquid</code><code>sections/starter-template-library.liquid</code></span>
        <span role="cell">Owns special storefront states and this internal documentation page.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="starter-library__group" id="library-templates">
    <header class="starter-library__heading">
      <p>Templates</p>
      <h2>Core page structures</h2>
    </header>

    <div class="starter-library__table" role="table">
      <div class="starter-library__row starter-library__row--head" role="row">
        <span role="columnheader">Template</span>
        <span role="columnheader">Path</span>
        <span role="columnheader">Purpose</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <span role="cell">Homepage</span>
        <code role="cell">templates/index.json</code>
        <span role="cell">Default landing page skeleton.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <span role="cell">Standard page</span>
        <code role="cell">templates/page.json</code>
        <span role="cell">Flexible page layout powered by Base section + container blocks.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <span role="cell">Product</span>
        <code role="cell">templates/product.json</code>
        <span role="cell">Product page with gallery, form, recommendations, recently viewed, and sticky add-to-cart.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <span role="cell">Collection</span>
        <code role="cell">templates/collection.json</code>
        <span role="cell">Product grid, filters, sorting, search, and pagination.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <span role="cell">Cart</span>
        <code role="cell">templates/cart.json</code>
        <span role="cell">Cart lines, notes, attributes, discounts, and checkout flow.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <span role="cell">Blog</span>
        <code role="cell">templates/blog.json</code>
        <span role="cell">Article listing with search, tags, and pagination.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <span role="cell">Article</span>
        <code role="cell">templates/article.json</code>
        <span role="cell">Article page with metadata, image, comments, and structured data.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <span role="cell">Search</span>
        <code role="cell">templates/search.json</code>
        <span role="cell">Search page with predictive search and mixed result cards.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <span role="cell">Contact page</span>
        <code role="cell">templates/page.contact.json</code>
        <span role="cell">Contact form page template.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <span role="cell">List collections</span>
        <code role="cell">templates/list-collections.json</code>
        <span role="cell">All collections grid with pagination.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <span role="cell">Starter library</span>
        <code role="cell">templates/page.starter-library.json</code>
        <span role="cell">This documentation and demo page.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <span role="cell">404</span>
        <code role="cell">templates/404.json</code>
        <span role="cell">Not-found page content and recovery links.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <span role="cell">Password</span>
        <code role="cell">templates/password.json</code>
        <span role="cell">Storefront password page for pre-launch or maintenance states.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="starter-library__row" role="row">
        <span role="cell">Gift card</span>
        <code role="cell">templates/gift_card.liquid</code>
        <span role="cell">Shopify gift card presentation layout.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="starter-library__group" id="library-snippets">
    <header class="starter-library__heading">
      <p>Snippets</p>
      <h2>Reusable Liquid building blocks</h2>
    </header>

    <div class="starter-library__note">
      <strong>Live snippet examples:</strong>
      the cards below call the actual files in <code>snippets/</code>. Non-visual snippets such as
      <code>meta-tags</code>, <code>css-variables</code>, and structured data helpers stay listed in the reference
      because rendering extra copies here would change page metadata instead of creating a useful visual preview.
    </div>

    <div class="starter-library-snippet-showcase">
      <article class="starter-library-snippet-card">
        <span>snippets/section-header.liquid</span>
        {% render 'section-header',
          eyebrow: 'Live snippet',
          heading: 'Section header',
          text: '<p>This heading is rendered through the shared section-header snippet.</p>',
          alignment: 'left'
        %}
      </article>

      <article class="starter-library-snippet-card">
        <span>snippets/main-button.liquid</span>
        {% render 'main-button', label: 'Primary action', url: routes.root_url, variant: 'primary' %}
        {% render 'main-button', label: 'Secondary action', url: routes.root_url, variant: 'secondary' %}
      </article>

      <article class="starter-library-snippet-card">
        <span>snippets/button-group.liquid</span>
        {% render 'button-group',
          primary_label: 'Shop now',
          primary_url: routes.root_url,
          primary_variant: 'primary',
          secondary_label: 'Learn more',
          secondary_url: routes.root_url,
          secondary_variant: 'secondary'
        %}
      </article>

      <article class="starter-library-snippet-card">
        <span>snippets/empty-state.liquid</span>
        {% render 'empty-state', text: 'This is the reusable editor empty-state snippet.' %}
      </article>

      <article class="starter-library-snippet-card">
        <span>snippets/cart-shipping-progress.liquid</span>
        {% render 'cart-shipping-progress',
          threshold: 100,
          class: 'starter-library-snippet-shipping-progress'
        %}
      </article>

      <article class="starter-library-snippet-card starter-library-snippet-card--wide">
        <span>snippets/form-field.liquid</span>
        <div class="starter-library-snippet-form-grid">
          {% render 'form-field',
            type: 'input',
            id: 'StarterSnippetName',
            name: 'contact[Name]',
            label: 'Name',
            placeholder: 'Alex Morgan',
            class: 'starter-library-snippet-field'
          %}
          {% render 'form-field',
            type: 'select',
            id: 'StarterSnippetTopic',
            name: 'contact[Topic]',
            label: 'Topic',
            placeholder: 'Choose a topic',
            options_text: starter_showcase_topic_options,
            class: 'starter-library-snippet-field'
          %}
          {% render 'form-field',
            type: 'radio',
            id: 'StarterSnippetPriority',
            name: 'contact[Priority]',
            label: 'Priority',
            options_text: starter_showcase_priority_options,
            class: 'starter-library-snippet-field',
            choices_class: 'starter-library-snippet-choices',
            choice_class: 'starter-library-snippet-choice'
          %}
          {% render 'form-field',
            type: 'checkbox',
            id: 'StarterSnippetConsent',
            name: 'contact[Consent]',
            label_html: starter_showcase_consent_label,
            checkbox_class: 'starter-library-snippet-consent',
            checkbox_label_class: 'starter-library-snippet-consent-label'
          %}
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="starter-library-snippet-card starter-library-snippet-card--wide">
        <span>snippets/newsletter-form.liquid + snippets/form-message.liquid</span>
        {% render 'newsletter-form',
          id: 'StarterSnippetNewsletter',
          class: 'starter-library-snippet-newsletter',
          row_class: 'starter-library-snippet-newsletter__row',
          button_label: 'Subscribe'
        %}
      </article>

      <article class="starter-library-snippet-card starter-library-snippet-card--wide">
        <span>snippets/predictive-search-form.liquid</span>
        {% render 'predictive-search-form',
          input_id: 'StarterSnippetSearch',
          panel_id: 'starter-snippet-predictive-search',
          types: 'product,page,article',
          class: 'starter-library-snippet-search',
          form_class: 'starter-library-snippet-search__form',
          row_class: 'starter-library-snippet-search__row',
          label: starter_search_label,
          input_value: '',
          placeholder: starter_search_placeholder,
          button_label: starter_search_submit,
          unavailable_products: 'last'
        %}
      </article>

      <article class="starter-library-snippet-card">
        <span>snippets/rating-stars.liquid</span>
        {% render 'rating-stars', rating: 5 %}
      </article>

      <article class="starter-library-snippet-card starter-library-snippet-card--wide">
        <span>snippets/product-price.liquid + product-badges + quick-add-form</span>
        {% if starter_demo_product != blank %}
          <div class="starter-library-snippet-commerce">
            <h3>{{ starter_demo_product.title | escape }}</h3>
            {% render 'product-price',
              price: starter_demo_product.price,
              compare_at_price: starter_demo_product.compare_at_price,
              class: 'starter-library-snippet-price'
            %}
            {% render 'product-badges', product: starter_demo_product %}
            {% render 'quick-add-form', product: starter_demo_product %}
          </div>
        {% else %}
          {% render 'empty-state', text: 'Add a product with handle gift-card to preview commerce snippets here.' %}
        {% endif %}
      </article>

      <article class="starter-library-snippet-card starter-library-snippet-card--wide">
        <span>snippets/product-card.liquid</span>
        {% if starter_demo_product != blank %}
          {% render 'product-card', product: starter_demo_product, show_badges: true, show_secondary_image: true, enable_quick_add: true %}
        {% else %}
          {% render 'empty-state', text: 'Product card needs a real product object.' %}
        {% endif %}
      </article>

      <article class="starter-library-snippet-card starter-library-snippet-card--wide">
        <span>snippets/article-card.liquid</span>
        {% if starter_demo_article != blank %}
          {% render 'article-card', article: starter_demo_article, show_image: true, show_excerpt: true, show_author: true, show_date: true, show_tags: true %}
        {% else %}
          {% render 'empty-state', text: 'Article card needs a real blog article.' %}
        {% endif %}
      </article>

      <article class="starter-library-snippet-card">
        <span>snippets/image.liquid</span>
        {% if starter_demo_product.featured_image != blank %}
          {% render 'image',
            image: starter_demo_product.featured_image,
            alt: starter_demo_product.title,
            width: 600,
            height: 600,
            crop: 'center'
          %}
        {% else %}
          {% render 'empty-state', text: 'Image snippet needs a real Shopify image object.' %}
        {% endif %}
      </article>

      <article class="starter-library-snippet-card">
        <span>snippets/pagination.liquid</span>
        {% paginate collections by 1 %}
          {% render 'pagination', paginate: paginate, class: 'starter-library-snippet-pagination' %}
        {% endpaginate %}
      </article>

      <article class="starter-library-snippet-card">
        <span>snippets/modal.liquid</span>
        {% render 'modal',
          id: 'starter-library-modal-showcase',
          trigger: starter_showcase_modal_trigger,
          title: 'Reusable modal',
          content: starter_showcase_modal_content
        %}
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="starter-library__grid starter-library__grid--small">
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Section header</h3>
        <code>snippets/section-header.liquid</code>
        <p>Shared heading, eyebrow, description, and alignment markup.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Main button</h3>
        <code>snippets/main-button.liquid</code>
        <p>Reusable button link with primary, secondary, and accent variants.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Cart shipping progress</h3>
        <code>snippets/cart-shipping-progress.liquid</code>
        <p>Reusable free-shipping progress message used by cart and cart drawer surfaces.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Modal</h3>
        <code>snippets/modal.liquid</code>
        <code>assets/modal.js</code>
        <p>Reusable dialog with a captured custom trigger and captured content slot.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Product card</h3>
        <code>snippets/product-card.liquid</code>
        <p>Product image, title, vendor, price, and compare-at price.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Article card</h3>
        <code>snippets/article-card.liquid</code>
        <p>Blog/article teaser card with image, metadata, excerpt, and tags.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Image</h3>
        <code>snippets/image.liquid</code>
        <p>Responsive image helper with optional link wrapper and loading controls.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Button group</h3>
        <code>snippets/button-group.liquid</code>
        <p>Shared one-or-two-button CTA wrapper that renders main button variants.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Empty state</h3>
        <code>snippets/empty-state.liquid</code>
        <p>Reusable dashed editor note for unconfigured sections and blocks.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Form field</h3>
        <code>snippets/form-field.liquid</code>
        <p>Common input, textarea, select, radio, and required checkbox renderer.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Form message</h3>
        <code>snippets/form-message.liquid</code>
        <p>Shared Shopify form success and validation error output.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Newsletter form</h3>
        <code>snippets/newsletter-form.liquid</code>
        <p>Reusable customer form tagged for newsletter subscriptions.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Pagination</h3>
        <code>snippets/pagination.liquid</code>
        <p>Shared wrapper around Shopify default pagination, with optional anchor support.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Predictive search form</h3>
        <code>snippets/predictive-search-form.liquid</code>
        <p>Reusable predictive-search form shell for search, blog, and collection routes.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Product badges</h3>
        <code>snippets/product-badges.liquid</code>
        <p>Sale and sold-out badge logic shared by product card displays.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Product price</h3>
        <code>snippets/product-price.liquid</code>
        <p>Current and compare-at price output for product cards and product pages.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Quick add form</h3>
        <code>snippets/quick-add-form.liquid</code>
        <p>Product-card quick add form with choose-options fallback.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Rating stars</h3>
        <code>snippets/rating-stars.liquid</code>
        <p>Accessible reusable star rating used by testimonial cards.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Meta tags</h3>
        <code>snippets/meta-tags.liquid</code>
        <p>SEO title, description, canonical, social tags, and structured data basics.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>CSS variables</h3>
        <code>snippets/css-variables.liquid</code>
        <p>Global theme CSS custom properties from theme settings.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Structured breadcrumbs</h3>
        <code>snippets/structured-data-breadcrumbs.liquid</code>
        <p>Breadcrumb JSON-LD for SEO-friendly page context.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="starter-library__group" id="library-assets">
    <header class="starter-library__heading">
      <p>Assets</p>
      <h2>JavaScript and CSS helpers</h2>
    </header>

    <div class="starter-library__grid starter-library__grid--small">
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Critical CSS</h3><code>assets/critical.css</code><p>Global reset, base styles, layout utilities, cart drawer, and shared theme primitives.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Header</h3><code>assets/header.js</code><p>Header drawer, search panel, and navigation interaction behavior.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Account icon</h3><code>assets/icon-account.svg</code><p>Reusable account icon used by header account entry points.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Cart icon</h3><code>assets/icon-cart.svg</code><p>Reusable cart icon used by header cart entry points.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Announcement bar</h3><code>assets/announcement-bar.js</code><p>Announcement marquee and promo-strip interaction behavior.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Cart</h3><code>assets/cart.js</code><p>Ajax cart, drawer, section rendering, cart count, notes, attributes, and discounts.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Collection</h3><code>assets/collection.js</code><p>Collection filtering, sorting, and product grid interaction helpers.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Contact form</h3><code>assets/contact-form.js</code><p>Client-side enhancements for the block-driven contact form.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Modal</h3><code>assets/modal.js</code><p>Reusable native dialog open, close, backdrop, and Escape behavior.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Product form</h3><code>assets/product-form.js</code><p>Ajax add-to-cart for product forms.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Product gallery</h3><code>assets/product-gallery.js</code><p>Product media thumbnail switching.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Product slider</h3><code>assets/product-slider.js</code><p>Swiper-backed product carousel initialization for product slider blocks.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Product variants</h3><code>assets/product-variant-selector.js</code><p>Variant option synchronization, media switching, and product form state updates.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Predictive search</h3><code>assets/predictive-search.js</code><code>assets/predictive-search.css</code><p>Keyboard-friendly predictive search dropdown.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Blog filters</h3><code>assets/blog.js</code><p>Blog tag select behavior.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Countdown promo</h3><code>assets/countdown-promo.js</code><p>Live countdown timer values.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>FAQ</h3><code>assets/faq.js</code><p>Animated details opening, closing, and chevron state.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Logo marquee</h3><code>assets/logo-marquee.js</code><p>Safe client-side marquee duplication for continuous logo rails.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Tabs</h3><code>assets/tabs.js</code><p>Accessible tab switching.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Testimonials</h3><code>assets/testimonials.js</code><p>Slider and interaction behavior for testimonial blocks.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Recommendations</h3><code>assets/product-recommendations.js</code><p>Fetches Shopify product recommendations section HTML.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Recently viewed</h3><code>assets/recently-viewed-products.js</code><p>Tracks product handles and renders recently viewed cards.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Sticky add to cart</h3><code>assets/sticky-add-to-cart.js</code><p>Shows a sticky product form after the main form scrolls away.</p></article>
      <article class="starter-library-card"><h3>Swiper bundle</h3><code>assets/swiper-bundle.min.js</code><code>assets/swiper-bundle.min.css</code><p>Vendor carousel library used by slider-like components.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="starter-library__group" id="library-blocks">
    <header class="starter-library__heading">
      <p>Theme blocks</p>
      <h2>Private child blocks</h2>
    </header>

    <div class="starter-library__note">
      <strong>Private child blocks:</strong>
      filenames that start with <code>_</code> are nested implementation blocks. Merchants add them through
      their parent component, not as standalone page content.
    </div>

    <div class="starter-library__grid starter-library__grid--small">
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Tab container</h3>
        <code>blocks/_tab.liquid</code>
        <p>Private nested container used by the Tabs section for flexible panel content.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Contact form fields</h3>
        <code>blocks/_contact-input.liquid</code>
        <code>blocks/_contact-select.liquid</code>
        <code>blocks/_contact-radio.liquid</code>
        <code>blocks/_contact-textarea.liquid</code>
        <code>blocks/_contact-consent.liquid</code>
        <p>Private nested field blocks used by the configurable Contact form block.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Content item blocks</h3>
        <code>blocks/_faq-item.liquid</code>
        <code>blocks/_comparison-row.liquid</code>
        <code>blocks/_testimonial.liquid</code>
        <p>Private rows/items that give parent components repeatable content.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="starter-library-card">
        <h3>Visual card blocks</h3>
        <code>blocks/_collection-card.liquid</code>
        <code>blocks/_promo-card.liquid</code>
        <code>blocks/_logo-item.liquid</code>
        <code>blocks/_trust-badge.liquid</code>
        <p>Private visual cards used by collection list, promo grid, logo marquee, and trust badge blocks.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</section>

{% stylesheet %}
  .starter-library {
    display: grid;
    gap: 2.5rem;
    padding-block: 3rem;
  }

  .starter-library__hero {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
    max-width: 860px;
  }

  .starter-library__hero h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 5rem);
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .starter-library__hero p {
    max-width: 70ch;
    color: rgb(92, 95, 98);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .starter-library__eyebrow,
  .starter-library__heading p,
  .starter-library-card > span {
    margin: 0;
    color: rgb(92, 95, 98);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .starter-library__route,
  .starter-library__note {
    padding: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid rgb(220, 220, 220);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: rgb(250, 251, 251);
  }

  .starter-library__route {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .starter-library__note {
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .starter-library__route span {
    color: rgb(92, 95, 98);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  .starter-library code {
    display: inline-block;
    min-width: 0;
    width: auto;
    max-width: 100%;
    overflow-wrap: anywhere;
    word-break: break-word;
    white-space: normal;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: rgb(244, 244, 245);
    color: rgb(32, 34, 35);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.35;
    vertical-align: baseline;
  }

  .starter-library__nav {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .starter-library__nav a {
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid rgb(220, 220, 220);
    border-radius: 4px;
    color: currentcolor;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .starter-library__summary {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(160px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .starter-library__summary > div {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.25rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid rgb(220, 220, 220);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .starter-library__summary strong {
    font-size: 2rem;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .starter-library__summary span {
    color: rgb(92, 95, 98);
  }

  .starter-library-snippet-showcase {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .starter-library-snippet-card {
    display: grid;
    align-content: start;
    gap: 1rem;
    min-width: 0;
    padding: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid rgb(220, 220, 220);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: white;
  }

  .starter-library-snippet-card--wide {
    grid-column: span 2;
  }

  .starter-library-snippet-card > span {
    color: rgb(92, 95, 98);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .starter-library-snippet-card .section-header {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .starter-library-snippet-form-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .starter-library-snippet-field {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.35rem;
  }

  .starter-library-snippet-field input,
  .starter-library-snippet-field select,
  .starter-library-snippet-newsletter input,
  .starter-library-snippet-search input {
    width: 100%;
    min-height: 42px;
    padding: 0.55rem 0.7rem;
    border: 1px solid rgb(180, 180, 180);
    border-radius: 4px;
    font: inherit;
  }

  .starter-library-snippet-choices {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .starter-library-snippet-choice,
  .starter-library-snippet-consent {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.55rem;
  }

  .starter-library-snippet-consent-label p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .starter-library-snippet-newsletter,
  .starter-library-snippet-search__form,
  .starter-library-snippet-commerce {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .starter-library-snippet-newsletter__row,
  .starter-library-snippet-search__row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) auto;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .starter-library-snippet-newsletter button,
  .starter-library-snippet-search button,
  .starter-library-snippet-commerce .quick-add__choose-options,
  .starter-library-snippet-commerce .quick-add input[type='submit'] {
    min-height: 42px;
    padding: 0.55rem 0.9rem;
    border: 1px solid rgb(20, 20, 20);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: rgb(20, 20, 20);
    color: white;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  .starter-library-snippet-price {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .starter-library-snippet-card .product-card,
  .starter-library-snippet-card .article-card {
    height: 100%;
  }

  .starter-library__guide-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(230px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .starter-library-guide-card {
    display: grid;
    align-content: start;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid rgb(220, 220, 220);
    border-radius: 12px;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgb(250, 251, 251), white);
  }

  .starter-library-guide-card > span {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 2rem;
    height: 2rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: rgb(32, 34, 35);
    color: white;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .starter-library-guide-card h3,
  .starter-library-guide-card p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .starter-library-guide-card p {
    color: rgb(92, 95, 98);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .starter-library__group {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    scroll-margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .starter-library__heading {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.35rem;
  }

  .starter-library__heading h2 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 4vw, 2.6rem);
  }

  .starter-library__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .starter-library__grid--small {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }

  .starter-library-card {
    display: grid;
    align-content: start;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    min-width: 0;
    padding: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid rgb(220, 220, 220);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: white;
  }

  .starter-library-card > span {
    order: 1;
  }

  .starter-library-card h3 {
    order: 2;
  }

  .starter-library-card p {
    order: 3;
  }

  .starter-library-card code {
    order: 4;
    justify-self: start;
  }

  .starter-library-card code:first-of-type {
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  .starter-library-card--featured {
    border-color: rgb(32, 34, 35);
    background: rgb(250, 251, 251);
    box-shadow: 0 12px 36px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  }

  .starter-library-card h3,
  .starter-library-card p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .starter-library-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .starter-library-card p {
    color: rgb(92, 95, 98);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .starter-library-modal-trigger {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.15rem;
    width: fit-content;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    border: 1px solid rgb(32, 34, 35);
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: rgb(32, 34, 35);
    color: white;
    font: inherit;
    text-align: left;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  .starter-library-modal-trigger small {
    opacity: 0.72;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
  }

  .starter-library__table {
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid rgb(220, 220, 220);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .starter-library__row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(140px, 0.6fr) minmax(220px, 0.9fr) minmax(240px, 1.5fr);
  }

  .starter-library__row > * {
    min-width: 0;
    padding: 0.85rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgb(220, 220, 220);
  }

  .starter-library__row > * + * {
    border-left: 1px solid rgb(220, 220, 220);
  }

  .starter-library__row--head {
    background: rgb(246, 246, 247);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .starter-library__row--head > * {
    border-top: 0;
  }

  @media screen and (max-width: 749px) {
    .starter-library-snippet-card--wide {
      grid-column: auto;
    }

    .starter-library-snippet-form-grid,
    .starter-library-snippet-newsletter__row,
    .starter-library-snippet-search__row {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .starter-library__table {
      overflow-x: auto;
    }

    .starter-library__row {
      min-width: 760px;
    }
  }
{% endstylesheet %}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Starter template library",
  "settings": [],
  "presets": [{ "name": "Starter template library" }]
}
{% endschema %}
